Package com.kuka.device

Contains common robotics-related classes and interfaces.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IAbsoluteAccuracy
    Capability interface that represents a robot which supports absolute accuracy.
    IControllerDevice
    Via this capability, devices managed by a controller provide an identifying name and enable access to their controller's capabilities.
    IElasticityCompensation
    Capability interface that represents a robot which supports elasticity compensation.
    IForceSensitiveRobot
    Functionality offered by robots measuring Cartesian forces.
    IHomePosition
    Interface providing home position related functionality.
    IJointDevice
    Interface providing functionality of a device with a number of rotating joints.
    IKinematicsCalculator
    Interface for kinematics calculation.
    IMovableDevice
    Provides information about the state of device that is able move.
    IMovableDeviceStateListener
    Listener interface for notifications about movable device states.
    IRobotPositionProvider
    Interface providing pose information of a robot.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ForceData
    This class provides the estimated external force respectively torque in a specific coordinate frame.
    JointLimits
    Describes the limits for joint angles of a IJointDevice.
    RoboticArm
    A RoboticArm is a device which can hold a tool and do some simple motions out of the box.

Package com.kuka.device Description

Contains common robotics-related classes and interfaces.
